    public class RTAtomicModelDescriptor
extends AtomicModelDescriptor
implements RTModelDescriptorI
    The class RTAtomicModelDescriptor describes real time atomic models in DEVS simulation architectures.

 post    RTAtomicModelDescriptor.checkInvariant(this)
        Parameters:
        modelClass - Java class defining the atomic model.
        modelURI - URI of the model to be created.
        importedEvents - events imported by the model.
        exportedEvents - events exported by the model.
        simulatedTimeUnit - time unit used for the simulation clock.
        amFactory - atomic model factory creating the model or null if none.
        engineCreationMode - creation mode for the simulation engine.
        schedulerProvider - lambda-expression which execution provides the real time scheduler to be set on the simulaiton engine of the model.
        accelerationFactor - for real time engines, the acceleration factor between the simulcation clock and the real time.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - to do.
